    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm trying to plan a trip from Heathrow to Edinburgh. I'm thinking of taking the Heathrow Express to Paddington, then catching an LNER train up to Edinburgh, and a bus for the last bit. How much buffer time should I leave between the Heathrow Express and the LNER train just to be safe? I don't want to miss my connection if there are delays.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A good buffer time between the Heathrow Express and the LNER train, say at least 45 minutes, is wise. This gives you enough room for a minor delay on the Express, or if the platform for the LNER is a bit of a mess, you won't be scrambling. Always check the schedule, though, as those schedules are often just suggestions, and you'll find a little wiggle room in the real world.",
