      "content": "Strikers, delays, and general train chaos are the usual suspects, of course. A real pain for any traveler, especially when you're trying to make a tight connection. You should always budget for at least an extra hour if you're feeling nervous, just in case. It's better to have extra time than to be stuck waiting for a train that's been delayed by a few hundred yards of unexpected shunting.",
      "source": "target",
